      <div class="d-flex justify-content-center text-center">
      <h3>Types of Pessaries</h3>
    </div>
    <div class="d-flex justify-content-center text-center">
      <p>There are several types of pessaries available, each designed to address specific types of prolapse and individual anatomical differences:</p>
    </div>
      <div class="row g-2 text-center pb-4">
        <div class="col-4">
          <h3 class="card-title h4">Ring Pessaries</h3>
          <p class="card-text">The most common type, suitable for mild to moderate prolapse. They provide support to the vaginal walls and pelvic organs.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-4">
          <h3 class="card-title h4">Cube Pessaries</h3>
          <p class="card-text">Used for more severe prolapse, these provide support through suction against the vaginal walls.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-4">
          <h3 class="card-title h4">Gellhorn Pessaries</h3>
          <p class="card-text">Designed for advanced prolapse, offering more substantial support for the pelvic organs.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-center">During your assessment, Sharon will determine which type and size of pessary is most appropriate for your specific condition, ensuring optimal comfort and effectiveness.</p>

    </div>
